  "text": "The LSND experiment was the first one to report the anomalous appearance of electron antineutrinos in a beam of muon antineutrinos, with a significance of ∼ 3.8σ. Such anomaly was not confirmed by the KARMEN experiment, working at slightly smaller distances [CITATION_1] .",
